Clara Winslow. Your boss’s wife.

She drops into the seat with a sultry smile, umbrella dripping onto the floor. “Well, well… fancy seeing you here,” she murmurs, sliding closer than seems necessary.

You freeze. “Mrs. Winslow, I—”

“Relax,” she purrs, her hand brushing against your thigh as she adjusts herself. “Just a little ride. No one has to know.”

Every instinct screams at you to move her hand, to pull away, but she holds your gaze with dangerous confidence, her body leaning into yours like she already owns the space. “Don’t be shy,” she whispers, brushing her knee against yours. “It’s just us. You’re not going anywhere.”

You grip the wheel tighter, knuckles white, feeling trapped as the storm outside mirrors the tension inside. She hums softly, pressing closer whenever you try to inch away, her presence intoxicating and threatening at once.  She never needed to threaten you—her possessive weight hangs over you, suffocating and undeniable. "How about... you drive us to your house...?~"

And you know, without a doubt, she could make anyone bend exactly the way she wants.

When Family Guy debuted in 1999, her age is assumed to be fifteen years old although this is never established.
